******
[6] Minnesota (Rice County, Stearns County): backyard, commercial flock
Date: Tue 26 Apr 2022 13:38 CDT
Source: West Central Tribune [edited]
https://www.wctrib.com/news/local/two-additional-avian-flu-diagnoses-bring-minnesota-to-60-infection-sites


Two additional avian flu diagnoses bring Minnesota to 60 infection sites. A confirmed diagnosis was received Saturday [23 Apr 2022] in a Rice County producer of 60 unspecified birds. And Stearns County now has its 8th site with a confirmed diagnosis on Monday [25 Apr 2022] at a commercial meat turkey operation of 14 590 birds.

The Board of Animal Health's tally of confirmed diagnoses of H5N1 highly pathogenic avian influenza now stands at 2 717 892 over 60 sites.

The Board of Animal Health's web page devoted to avian flu response in the state -- which can be found at http://www.bah.state.mn.us/hpai -- is updated by noon each weekday with the information that is known about poultry infection sites. Data from previous days also may be updated by quality control staff if more accurate information is gathered later.

According to the web page, commercial meat turkey operations remain the vast majority of the sites. There are now 5 sites in the backyard producer category; 3 sites of commercial turkey breeder hens, all located in Kandiyohi County; and 2 chicken flocks in Morrison County, one broiler and one egg layer operation.

[Byline: Susan Lunneborg]

