******
[7] Michigan (Wexford County): backyard poultry
Date: Thu 28 Apr 2022 14:54 EDT
Source: Michigan Live [abridged, edited]
https://www.mlive.com/news/2022/04/bird-flu-confirmed-in-wexford-county-poultry-flock.html


Bird flu has been confirmed in another Michigan county. According to the Michigan Department of Agriculture and Rural Development (MDARD), the disease known as highly pathogenic avian influenza was detected in a non-commercial backyard poultry flock from Wexford County.

The flock contained approximately 60 birds of various species. The birds will be killed to prevent disease spread. The MDARD says the latest positive test emphasizes the ongoing high risk for the disease in Michigan and underscores the need for bird owners to maintain their vigilance in protecting their flocks.

The Wexford County flock is the latest in Michigan to have a confirmed positive test. The disease was confirmed in a flock of 35 poultry housed in Saginaw County this week. State officials reported cases of bird flu in Kalamazoo County in February, in Macomb County in March, and in Livingston, Menominee and Washtenaw counties in April [2022]. Multiple counties in northern Indiana have also had confirmed cases.

[Byline: Brandon Champion]

